            "bio": "Jim Yong Choi is a PGA Class “A” Member who has over 20+ years combined golf professional, teaching and business management experience. His passion for golf began to grow in his early 20s, when he first began to play in New Jersey, and has expanded throughout his time in both the Northeast and the South.\n\nJim owns and manages the Northcrest Driving Range, which focuses on providing a multi-functional facility that provides a safe and engaging environment to learn golf. He also manages the recently renovated Northcrest Golf Pro Shop, which is a licensed provider for Callaway, Cleveland, Honma, Majestic, Mizuno, MU, Srixon, TaylorMade, XXIO golf gear. He is also frequently featured on the KTN news station and Atlanta Radio Korea as the resident golf expert. He teaches a wide range of individuals, from beginners to advanced golfers, and has expertise in improving the accuracy and consistency of your short game.\n\nAlongside his passion for golf, Jim enjoys outdoor activities such as hiking, soccer, and pickleball, and spending time with his family and dog Ralphie that you may see roaming the driving range on occasion.",
