            "photo": "shopify://shop_images/Ah_Ram_Suh_Headshot_2.jpg",
            "bio": "Ah Ram Suh brings an exceptional blend of elite competition, coaching excellence, and educational leadership to Northcrest Golf. A Class A LPGA Member since 2009 and LPGA Coach of the Year in 2018, she’s known for helping golfers unlock accuracy, confidence, and power through personalized instruction.\n\nHer competitive career includes three professional victories on the KLPGA Tour between 1995 and 2004, following standout performances as a member of Korea’s Amateur National Team from 1992 to 1994. She captured titles at both the Hanju Ellesse Professional Open and the Korea Women’s Amateur Championship in 1991.\n\nAh Ram’s leadership in golf education includes serving as KLPGA Education Chairperson (2010–2012) and Director (2014–2017), roles in which she shaped player development across Korea. From 2013 to 2015, she coached the Korea National Team, combining high-level strategy with proven techniques to elevate performance across age groups. She holds a Ph.D. in Exercise Physiology from Yonsei University and is certified in TPI Golf Mechanics Level 2 and TPI Junior Performance Level 2—giving her a distinct edge in biomechanics and junior coaching.\n\nWhether you’re new to the game or chasing precision in tournament play, Ah Ram offers a training experience that’s rooted in excellence, energy, and genuine care.",
